text: Teoc Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Alabama and Mississippi. It is a tributary to the Sucarnoochee River. Teoc is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "pine". Variant names are "Teah Creek", "Teark Creek", "Teock Creek", "Teoe Creek", and "Tioch Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Sumter County, Alabama Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Kemper County, Mississippi
title: Teoc Creek (Sucarnoochee River tributary)
